cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.AI

This paper discusses a new capability added to ACL2, a theorem proving system based on first-order logic, which allows the correctness proofs of simplifiers to assume the correctness of certain proof tools and extracted facts. This falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of metafunctions and clause processors, which are related to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The examples given in the paper involve machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI).
